I came in here, was nicely greeting by two employees, and then informed about a buy one get one free deal for the Steak and Cheese sub. I looked towards the back counter, and saw two subs already made, wrapped and ready to go.  Why are you trying to sell me your mistakes? Is $5 really that important to your end of day sales? Why can't you let your employees eat the sandwich? That's what I did when I worked in food service. Oh, this piece of chocolate is cracked. I can't sell it, so I'll eat it. Oh, this piece of chocolate is not shiny enough. I'll eat it.  If your employees don't want the sandwich, you can offer it to a homeless guy on the street, but don't try to sell it to me!

I was leaving from a convention on Labor day weekend and me and my mom had a date night. So before we board on metro, we decided to get something from Subway. As soon as they came to our service, we were flat out disrespected by the employees. When I was trying to make a decision with my mom, the guy lashed out and told us to hurry up. Then things started to get out of hand, another guy asked us for our toppings for our subs. As soon as we got to the guy, he literally didn't even bother paying attention and just only threw the lettuce and onions very harshly instead of listening to us. Got to the cashier, he seem to over rang me for 4 cookies when I asked for only three. I asked him why, then gave me a very rude answer and told me to respect your culture and learn to talk to me in a right way. Right way?  Who are they to tell me when they dont even have manners themselves? I am a customer and I should be treated right. This is where they were all telling customers harsh comments. So we decided to brush off and sit for a min then we felt uncomfortable. I did call up corporate then got a response from store manager who still wasn't helpful. Sorry to write all but this was by far the worst subway restaurant I've ever been to.
